	     Johannesburg – The body of Egyptian national Mohamed Ahmed Nawar, who went missing on October 2, was found buried at a nature reserve north of Marble Hall of Friday. Limpopo police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said Nawar was robbed of his car and killed. Three suspects have been arrested and will appear in court on Monday on charges of murder and robbery.Ngoepe said police investigations were continuing. The discovery comes after an intelligence-driven operation by Marble Hall detectives and Groblersdal crime intelligence. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  